[6] New Caledonia
Date: Mon 29 Sep 2008
Source: ABC (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) Radio Australia [edited]
<http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/news/stories/200809/s2376908.htm?tab=3D=pacific>


Health officials in New Caledonia say the number of reported cases of
dengue fever has now reached 1000.

The department says the outbreak overwhelmingly concerns the [dengue
virus] type 1 variety [serotype].

It says this is in contrast to several neighbouring Pacific island
countries, such as Fiji, Kiribati, Samoa, and American Samoa where
the epidemic has been identified as one of [dengue virus] type 4.

Health authorities in both New Caledonian and French Polynesia, say
they are on the alert for visitors or returning travellers, who could
"import" the disease [virus].

Public spraying campaigns have also been carried out in the past
month, especially in the capital Nouma and its suburbs.

--
